>I have had a sore throat for almost a week.  When I look int>the mirror with the aid of a flash light, I see white plaques i>the very back of my throat (on the sides).  I went to a healt>center to have a throat culture taken.  They said that I do no>have strep throat.  Could a viral infection cause white plaque>on the sides of my throatFirst, I am not a doctor.  I know about this because I have beethrough itIt sounds like tonsilitis (lit. swollen tonsils).  Feel under your jahinge for a swelling on each side.  If you find them, its tonsilitisI've had this a couple of times in the past.  The doctor prescribed weeks course of penicillin and that cleared it upIn my case it was associated with glandular fever, which is a virainfection which (from my point of view) resembled flu and tonsilitithat kept coming back for a year or so.  There is a blood test fothisIn conclusion, see a doctor (if you have not done so already)Paul--Paul Johnson (paj@gec-mrc.co.uk).\t    | Tel: +44 245 73331 ext 324--------------------------------------------+---------------------------------These ideas and others like them can be had | GEC-Marconi Research is nofor $0.02 each from any reputable idealist. | responsible for my opinion